Now I have all 13 files. Let me analyze and consolidate them into a single migration representing the final state.

Here is the complete consolidated SQL migration:

```sql
-- =============================================================================
-- CONSOLIDATED MIGRATION FOR HABITATV5
-- =============================================================================
-- Combines all 13 migrations (20260111 through 20260225) into a single
-- idempotent migration representing the final database state.
-- =============================================================================

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 1: EXTENSIONS
-- =============================================================================

CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "pg_graphql";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "pg_stat_statements" WITH SCHEMA "extensions";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "pgcrypto" WITH SCHEMA "extensions";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "plpgsql";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "supabase_vault";
CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS "uuid-ossp" WITH SCHEMA "extensions";

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 2: CUSTOM TYPES
-- =============================================================================

DO $$ BEGIN
    CREATE TYPE public.app_role AS ENUM ('admin', 'participant');
EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL;
END $$;

DO $$ BEGIN
    CREATE TYPE public.event_status AS ENUM ('draft', 'scheduled', 'active', 'paused', 'completed');
EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL;
END $$;

DO $$ BEGIN
    CREATE TYPE public.sprint_phase AS ENUM ('waiting', 'phase_1', 'phase_2', 'phase_3', 'phase_4', 'completed');
EXCEPTION WHEN duplicate_object THEN NULL;
END $$;

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 3: FUNCTIONS
-- =============================================================================

-- Auto-create a profile row when a new auth user is created
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.handle_new_user() RETURNS trigger
    LANGUAGE plpgsql SECURITY DEFINER
    SET search_path TO 'public'
    AS $$
BEGIN
    INSERT INTO public.profiles (user_id, full_name)
    VALUES (NEW.id, NEW.raw_user_meta_data->>'full_name');
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Check whether a user has a given app_role
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.has_role(_user_id uuid, _role public.app_role) RETURNS boolean
    LANGUAGE sql STABLE SECURITY DEFINER
    SET search_path TO 'public'
    AS $$
    SELECT EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM public.user_roles
        WHERE user_id = _user_id AND role = _role
    )
$$;

-- Check whether a user is a member of a given team
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.is_team_member(_user_id uuid, _team_id uuid) RETURNS boolean
    LANGUAGE sql STABLE SECURITY DEFINER
    SET search_path TO 'public'
    AS $$
    SELECT EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM public.team_members
        WHERE user_id = _user_id AND team_id = _team_id
    )
$$;

-- Generic updated_at timestamp trigger function
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column() RETURNS trigger
    LANGUAGE plpgsql
    SET search_path TO 'public'
    AS $$
BEGIN
    NEW.updated_at = now();
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Auto-assign admin role to the very first user who signs up
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.assign_first_admin()
RETURNS TRIGGER
LANGUAGE plpgsql
SECURITY DEFINER
SET search_path = public
AS $$
BEGIN
    IF NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM public.user_roles WHERE role = 'admin') THEN
        INSERT INTO public.user_roles (user_id, role)
        VALUES (NEW.id, 'admin');
    END IF;
    RETURN NEW;
END;
$$;

-- Dedicated updated_at trigger function for sprint_timer
CREATE OR REPLACE FUNCTION public.update_sprint_timer_updated_at()
RETURNS TRIGGER AS $$
BEGIN
  NEW.updated_at = now();
  RETURN NEW;
END;
$$ LANGUAGE plpgsql SET search_path = public;

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 4: TABLES
-- =============================================================================

-- Profiles -------------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.profiles (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    user_id uuid NOT NULL,
    full_name text,
    avatar_url text,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT profiles_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT profiles_user_id_key UNIQUE (user_id)
);

-- User Roles -----------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.user_roles (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    user_id uuid NOT NULL,
    role public.app_role NOT NULL,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT user_roles_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT user_roles_user_id_role_key UNIQUE (user_id, role)
);

-- Events ---------------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.events (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    title text NOT NULL,
    description text,
    scheduled_date timestamp with time zone NOT NULL,
    status public.event_status DEFAULT 'draft'::public.event_status NOT NULL,
    current_phase public.sprint_phase DEFAULT 'waiting'::public.sprint_phase NOT NULL,
    phase_started_at timestamp with time zone,
    created_by uuid,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT events_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id)
);

-- Event Registrations --------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.event_registrations (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    event_id uuid NOT NULL,
    user_id uuid NOT NULL,
    registered_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT event_registrations_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT event_registrations_event_id_user_id_key UNIQUE (event_id, user_id)
);

-- Teams (includes track column from migration 13) ----------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.teams (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    event_id uuid,
    name text NOT NULL,
    invite_code text DEFAULT "substring"(md5((random())::text), 1, 8),
    created_by uuid,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    password_hash text,
    track text DEFAULT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT teams_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT teams_invite_code_key UNIQUE (invite_code)
);

-- Team Members ---------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.team_members (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    team_id uuid NOT NULL,
    user_id uuid NOT NULL,
    joined_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT team_members_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT team_members_team_id_user_id_key UNIQUE (team_id, user_id)
);

-- Team Member Names (anonymous name storage) ---------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.team_member_names (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    team_id uuid NOT NULL,
    name text NOT NULL,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT team_member_names_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id)
);

-- Task Progress --------------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.task_progress (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    team_id uuid NOT NULL,
    phase public.sprint_phase NOT NULL,
    task_key text NOT NULL,
    completed boolean DEFAULT false NOT NULL,
    completed_by uuid,
    completed_at timestamp with time zone,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    content text,
    content_type text DEFAULT 'text'::text,
    CONSTRAINT task_progress_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id),
    CONSTRAINT task_progress_team_id_phase_task_key_key UNIQUE (team_id, phase, task_key)
);

-- Team Deliverables ----------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.team_deliverables (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    team_id uuid NOT NULL,
    type text NOT NULL,
    title text NOT NULL,
    url text,
    notes text,
    created_by uuid,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT team_deliverables_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id)
);

-- Customer Segments ----------------------------------------------------------
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.customer_segments (
    id uuid DEFAULT gen_random_uuid() NOT NULL,
    team_id uuid NOT NULL,
    name text NOT NULL,
    company_type text NOT NULL,
    job_titles text[] DEFAULT '{}'::text[] NOT NULL,
    why_they_care text NOT NULL,
    is_custom boolean DEFAULT false NOT NULL,
    created_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone DEFAULT now() NOT NULL,
    CONSTRAINT customer_segments_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id)
);

-- Sprint Timer (global singleton timer with all columns from migrations 5-11) -
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.sprint_timer (
    id uuid NOT NULL DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
    status text NOT NULL DEFAULT 'stopped' CHECK (status IN ('stopped', 'running', 'paused')),
    duration_seconds integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 14400,
    started_at timestamp with time zone,
    paused_at timestamp with time zone,
    elapsed_before_pause integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
    updated_at timestamp with time zone NOT NULL DEFAULT now(),
    display_phase public.sprint_phase NOT NULL DEFAULT 'waiting',
    promo_code text,
    app_link text DEFAULT NULL,
    display_image_url text NULL,
    CONSTRAINT sprint_timer_pkey PRIMARY KEY (id)
);

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 5: FOREIGN KEY CONSTRAINTS
-- =============================================================================

-- profiles
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.profiles
    ADD CONSTRAINT profiles_user_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- user_roles
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.user_roles
    ADD CONSTRAINT user_roles_user_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- events
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.events
    ADD CONSTRAINT events_created_by_fkey FOREIGN KEY (created_by) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;

-- event_registrations
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.event_registrations
    ADD CONSTRAINT event_registrations_event_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES public.events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.event_registrations
    ADD CONSTRAINT event_registrations_user_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- teams
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.teams
    ADD CONSTRAINT teams_event_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (event_id) REFERENCES public.events(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.teams
    ADD CONSTRAINT teams_created_by_fkey FOREIGN KEY (created_by) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;

-- team_members
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.team_members
    ADD CONSTRAINT team_members_team_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES public.teams(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.team_members
    ADD CONSTRAINT team_members_user_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- team_member_names
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.team_member_names
    ADD CONSTRAINT team_member_names_team_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES public.teams(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- task_progress
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.task_progress
    ADD CONSTRAINT task_progress_team_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES public.teams(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.task_progress
    ADD CONSTRAINT task_progress_completed_by_fkey FOREIGN KEY (completed_by) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;

-- team_deliverables
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.team_deliverables
    ADD CONSTRAINT team_deliverables_team_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES public.teams(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.team_deliverables
    ADD CONSTRAINT team_deliverables_created_by_fkey FOREIGN KEY (created_by) REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL;

-- customer_segments
ALTER TABLE ONLY public.customer_segments
    ADD CONSTRAINT customer_segments_team_id_fkey FOREIGN KEY (team_id) REFERENCES public.teams(id) ON DELETE CASCADE;

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 6: INDEXES
-- =============================================================================

CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_customer_segments_team_id ON public.customer_segments USING btree (team_id);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_teams_name_event ON public.teams USING btree (name, event_id);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_team_member_names_team_id ON public.team_member_names USING btree (team_id);

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 7: TRIGGERS
-- =============================================================================

-- updated_at triggers
CREATE TRIGGER update_customer_segments_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.customer_segments FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_events_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.events FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_profiles_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.profiles FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_task_progress_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.task_progress FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_team_deliverables_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.team_deliverables FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_teams_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.teams FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_updated_at_column();
CREATE TRIGGER update_sprint_timer_updated_at BEFORE UPDATE ON public.sprint_timer FOR EACH ROW EXECUTE FUNCTION public.update_sprint_timer_updated_at();

-- Auto-assign admin to the first user who registers
CREATE TRIGGER on_auth_user_created_assign_admin
    AFTER INSERT ON auth.users
    FOR EACH ROW
    EXECUTE FUNCTION public.assign_first_admin();

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 8: ROW LEVEL SECURITY - ENABLE
-- =============================================================================

ALTER TABLE public.profiles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.user_roles ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.events ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.event_registrations ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.teams ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.team_members ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.team_member_names ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.task_progress ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.team_deliverables ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.customer_segments ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
ALTER TABLE public.sprint_timer ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 9: RLS POLICIES - profiles
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Users can view all profiles" ON public.profiles
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Users can insert own profile" ON public.profiles
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK ((auth.uid() = user_id));

CREATE POLICY "Users can update own profile" ON public.profiles
    FOR UPDATE TO authenticated USING ((auth.uid() = user_id));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 10: RLS POLICIES - user_roles
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Admins can manage roles" ON public.user_roles
    TO authenticated USING (public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::public.app_role));

CREATE POLICY "Users can view own roles" ON public.user_roles
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING ((auth.uid() = user_id));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 11: RLS POLICIES - events
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Admins can manage events" ON public.events
    TO authenticated USING (public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::public.app_role));

CREATE POLICY "Creators can manage own events" ON public.events
    TO authenticated USING ((created_by = auth.uid()));

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can view scheduled events" ON public.events
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated
    USING (((status <> 'draft'::public.event_status) OR (created_by = auth.uid())));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 12: RLS POLICIES - event_registrations
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Admins can view all registrations" ON public.event_registrations
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::public.app_role));

CREATE POLICY "Users can register for events" ON public.event_registrations
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK ((auth.uid() = user_id));

CREATE POLICY "Users can unregister" ON public.event_registrations
    FOR DELETE TO authenticated USING ((auth.uid() = user_id));

CREATE POLICY "Users can view own registrations" ON public.event_registrations
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING ((auth.uid() = user_id));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 13: RLS POLICIES - teams
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can view teams" ON public.teams
    FOR SELECT USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Event participants can view teams" ON public.teams
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Admins can view all teams" ON public.teams
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated
    USING (public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'));

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can create teams" ON public.teams
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (true);

CREATE POLICY "Authenticated users can create teams" ON public.teams
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK ((auth.uid() = created_by));

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can update teams" ON public.teams
    FOR UPDATE USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Team creators can update teams" ON public.teams
    FOR UPDATE TO authenticated USING ((created_by = auth.uid()));

CREATE POLICY "Admins can update all teams" ON public.teams
    FOR UPDATE USING (has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::app_role));

CREATE POLICY "Admins can delete all teams" ON public.teams
    FOR DELETE USING (has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::app_role));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 14: RLS POLICIES - team_members
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Team members can view members" ON public.team_members
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated
    USING ((public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id) OR (auth.uid() = user_id)));

CREATE POLICY "Users can join teams" ON public.team_members
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK ((auth.uid() = user_id));

CREATE POLICY "Users can leave teams" ON public.team_members
    FOR DELETE TO authenticated USING ((auth.uid() = user_id));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 15: RLS POLICIES - team_member_names
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can view team member names" ON public.team_member_names
    FOR SELECT USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can insert team member names" ON public.team_member_names
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (true);

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 16: RLS POLICIES - task_progress
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can view task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR SELECT USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can insert task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (true);

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can update task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR UPDATE USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Anyone can delete task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR DELETE USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Team members can view progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can update progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can modify progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR UPDATE TO authenticated USING (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

CREATE POLICY "Admins can view all task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated
    USING (public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'));

CREATE POLICY "Admins can delete all task progress" ON public.task_progress
    FOR DELETE USING (has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin'::app_role));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 17: RLS POLICIES - team_deliverables
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Team members can view deliverables" ON public.team_deliverables
    FOR SELECT TO authenticated USING (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can add deliverables" ON public.team_deliverables
    FOR INSERT TO authenticated WITH CHECK (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can update deliverables" ON public.team_deliverables
    FOR UPDATE TO authenticated USING (public.is_team_member(auth.uid(), team_id));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 18: RLS POLICIES - customer_segments
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Team members can view their team segments" ON public.customer_segments
    FOR SELECT USING (((EXISTS ( SELECT 1
       FROM public.team_members
      WHERE ((team_members.team_id = customer_segments.team_id) AND (team_members.user_id = auth.uid())))) OR (EXISTS ( SELECT 1
       FROM public.teams
      WHERE (teams.id = customer_segments.team_id)))));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can insert segments for their team" ON public.customer_segments
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (((EXISTS ( SELECT 1
       FROM public.team_members
      WHERE ((team_members.team_id = customer_segments.team_id) AND (team_members.user_id = auth.uid())))) OR true));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can update their team segments" ON public.customer_segments
    FOR UPDATE USING (((EXISTS ( SELECT 1
       FROM public.team_members
      WHERE ((team_members.team_id = customer_segments.team_id) AND (team_members.user_id = auth.uid())))) OR true));

CREATE POLICY "Team members can delete their team segments" ON public.customer_segments
    FOR DELETE USING (((EXISTS ( SELECT 1
       FROM public.team_members
      WHERE ((team_members.team_id = customer_segments.team_id) AND (team_members.user_id = auth.uid())))) OR true));

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 19: RLS POLICIES - sprint_timer
-- =============================================================================

CREATE POLICY "Everyone can view timer" ON public.sprint_timer
    FOR SELECT USING (true);

CREATE POLICY "Admins can update timer" ON public.sprint_timer
    FOR UPDATE USING (
      EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM public.user_roles
        WHERE user_roles.user_id = auth.uid()
        AND user_roles.role = 'admin'
      )
    );

CREATE POLICY "Admins can insert timer" ON public.sprint_timer
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (
      EXISTS (
        SELECT 1 FROM public.user_roles
        WHERE user_roles.user_id = auth.uid()
        AND user_roles.role = 'admin'
      )
    );

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 20: STORAGE BUCKETS AND POLICIES
-- =============================================================================

INSERT INTO storage.buckets (id, name, public)
VALUES ('display-images', 'display-images', true)
ON CONFLICT (id) DO NOTHING;

CREATE POLICY "Public can view display images" ON storage.objects
    FOR SELECT USING (bucket_id = 'display-images');

CREATE POLICY "Admins can upload display images" ON storage.objects
    FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (
      bucket_id = 'display-images'
      AND public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin')
    );

CREATE POLICY "Admins can update display images" ON storage.objects
    FOR UPDATE USING (
      bucket_id = 'display-images'
      AND public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin')
    );

CREATE POLICY "Admins can delete display images" ON storage.objects
    FOR DELETE USING (
      bucket_id = 'display-images'
      AND public.has_role(auth.uid(), 'admin')
    );

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 21: REALTIME PUBLICATION
-- =============================================================================

ALTER PUBLICATION supabase_realtime ADD TABLE public.teams;
ALTER PUBLICATION supabase_realtime ADD TABLE public.task_progress;
ALTER PUBLICATION supabase_realtime ADD TABLE public.sprint_timer;

-- =============================================================================
-- SECTION 22: SEED DATA
-- =============================================================================

-- Insert the singleton sprint timer row
INSERT INTO public.sprint_timer (id) VALUES ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001')
ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;

-- Ensure the default admin user exists (idempotent)
INSERT INTO public.user_roles (user_id, role)
SELECT id, 'admin'::app_role FROM auth.users WHERE email = 'habitat@example.com'
ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING;
```

---

**Summary of what was consolidated:**

1. **Migration 1** (pg_dump): Base schema -- extensions, 3 enum types, 4 functions, 9 tables (profiles, user_roles, events, event_registrations, teams, team_members, task_progress, team_deliverables, customer_segments), all constraints, indexes, triggers, foreign keys, and RLS policies.

2. **Migration 2**: Added realtime publication for `teams` and `task_progress`; added admin SELECT policies on those tables.

3. **Migration 3**: Added `assign_first_admin()` function and trigger on `auth.users`.

4. **Migration 4**: Added admin UPDATE/DELETE policies on `teams` and admin DELETE policy on `task_progress`.

5. **Migration 5**: Created `sprint_timer` table with RLS, singleton row, realtime, and its own `updated_at` trigger.

6. **Migration 6**: Added `display_phase` and `promo_code` columns to `sprint_timer` -- folded into the CREATE TABLE.

7. **Migration 7**: Created `team_member_names` table with RLS and index.

8. **Migration 8**: Added `app_link` column to `sprint_timer` -- folded into the CREATE TABLE.

9. **Migration 9**: Added admin INSERT policy on `sprint_timer`.

10. **Migration 10**: Added `display_image_url` column to `sprint_timer` -- folded into the CREATE TABLE.

11. **Migration 11**: Created `display-images` storage bucket and 4 storage object policies.

12. **Migration 12**: Added `track` column to `teams` -- folded into the CREATE TABLE.

13. **Migration 13**: Re-created the admin trigger (was missing) and seeded admin role for `habitat@example.com` -- the trigger is already in section 7 and the seed is in section 22.

All ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN statements from later migrations have been folded directly into their respective CREATE TABLE statements so the tables are created with their final schema in one pass.
